Sentencas: In this study, a simple and cost-effective dry-pressing method has been used to fabricate a symmetrical solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) where the dense yttria-stabilized zirconia (YSZ) electrolyte film is sandwiched between two symmetrical porous YSZ layers in which La0.75Sr0.25Cr0.5Mn0.5O3-delta (LSCM) based anode and cathode are incorporated using wet impregnation techniques.
Titulo: A symmetrical solid oxide fuel cell prepared by dry-pressing and impregnating methods

Sentencas: The maximum power densities (P-max) of a single cell with 32 wt.% LSCM impregnated YSZ anode and cathode reach 333 and 265 mW cm(-2) at 900 degrees C in dry H-2 and CH4, respectively.
Titulo: A symmetrical solid oxide fuel cell prepared by dry-pressing and impregnating methods

Sentencas: The cell performance is further improved with additional impregnation of a small amount of Sm-doped CeO2 (SDC) or Ni.
Titulo: A symmetrical solid oxide fuel cell prepared by dry-pressing and impregnating methods

Sentencas: When 6 wt.% Ni as catalyst is added to both the anode and cathode.
Titulo: A symmetrical solid oxide fuel cell prepared by dry-pressing and impregnating methods

Sentencas: P-max values of 559 and 547 mW cm(-2) can be achieved, which are better than with SDC.
Titulo: A symmetrical solid oxide fuel cell prepared by dry-pressing and impregnating methods

Sentencas: The effect of Ni on the cathode performance is also investigated by impedance spectra analysis.
Titulo: A symmetrical solid oxide fuel cell prepared by dry-pressing and impregnating methods
